---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components'
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About — Zee Marquez"
	description="Zee Marquez — mechanical engineer, renewable energy specialist, AI builder, and finance student. Bridging hard engineering, intelligent systems, and project finance."
>
	<main class="app-container pt-36 pb-4">
		<h1 class="text-6xl pb-2 font-bold">About Me</h1>
	</main>

	<section class="app-container py-8 mb-4">
		<div class="prose prose-neutral prose-lg md:prose-xl dark:prose-invert prose-img:rounded-xl prose-figure:text-center prose-img:mx-auto max-w-3xl">

			<p>
				I'm <strong>Zee Marquez</strong> — a Mechanical Engineer who has spent the last few
				years at the crossroads of <strong>renewable energy, intelligent systems, and software</strong>.
				I build things end-to-end: from structural FEM analysis and PCB design to ML pipelines,
				cloud infrastructure, and full-stack applications. Right now I'm adding a new layer —
				studying <strong>Project Finance and M&amp;A</strong> to understand how the deals that
				fund the energy transition actually work.
			</p>
			<p>
				The common thread is the energy sector. I've done structural consulting on solar
				trackers and wind towers, launched an award-winning IoT startup for solar PV predictive
				maintenance, and built data tools and dashboards for renewable energy analysis. I find it
				fascinating to operate across the full stack of a problem: the physics, the code, and
				now the capital.
			</p>
			<p>
				Outside of work I write on this blog about the technical rabbit holes I fall into —
				blockchains, finite element methods, AI — and I build personal projects that scratch
				whatever itch I have at the time.
			</p>

			<!-- Experience -->
			<h2>Experience</h2>

			<h3>Technical Manager — Vulkano Engineering <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Madrid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Nov 2023 – Present</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Structural consulting on solar tracker and photovoltaic structures — detailed structural and frequency analysis to ensure design integrity under static and dynamic loads.</li>
				<li>Wind load analysis on solar panels and trackers, optimising for aerodynamic stability and material efficiency.</li>
				<li>Designed and delivered <strong>STOWAI</strong> end-to-end — from hardware concept and IoT sensor electronics to cloud deployment — in under 4 months. Secured awards from Actua UPM, CAM, Wayra, and La Caixa.</li>
				<li>Built client-facing real-time dashboards for asset performance monitoring.</li>
				<li>Registered utility model <strong>ES1315071U</strong> for a self-powered mechanical monitoring and predictive maintenance device.</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Structural Engineer — GRI · Gestamp Renewable Industries <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Madrid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Jan 2023 – Oct 2023</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Reduced manufacturing material costs by <strong>10%</strong> by implementing topology optimisation algorithms within FEM-based parametric tools for wind tower design.</li>
				<li>Migrated legacy FEM/CFD workflows to open-source alternatives, cutting licensing costs and improving automation.</li>
				<li>Resolved critical manufacturing discrepancies using targeted FEM simulations.</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Software & Control Engineering Intern — +D (masdediagram) <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Madrid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Jun 2019 – Jan 2021</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Programmed PLCs and developed software for crash testing and certification machines.</li>
				<li>Designed and assembled industrial automation control systems.</li>
			</ul>

			<!-- Education -->
			<h2>Education</h2>

			<h3>Project Finance and M&amp;A Master — ISBIF <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Jan 2026 – Present</span></h3>
			<p>
				Covering project finance structuring, leveraged buyouts, infrastructure financing,
				and M&amp;A deal mechanics — with a focus on the energy and infrastructure sectors.
			</p>

			<h3>BSc Mechanical Engineering (English) — Universidad Carlos III de Madrid <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· 2018 – 2022</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Exchange semesters at Case Western Reserve University and California State University Long Beach (USA) — 4.0 GPA.</li>
				<li>Honors in Physics and Python programming.</li>
				<li>University Moto-Student Team: designed sensorisation and data acquisition systems for racing motorcycles.</li>
			</ul>

			<!-- Skills -->
			<h2>Skills</h2>

			<h3>Energy &amp; Engineering</h3>
			<p>Finite Element Method (Abaqus, HyperWorks, ANSYS, CALCULIX), CFD (OpenFoam, Fluent), structural analysis (SAP, Revit), CAD (SolidWorks, CATIA, FreeCAD), topology optimisation, fatigue life prediction, wind load analysis, Eurocodes, DNV compliance.</p>

			<h3>Software, AI &amp; Data</h3>
			<p>Python, C#, C++, MATLAB · AI/ML model development, predictive maintenance algorithms, NLP, deep learning · Backend (FastAPI, Django, GraphQL) · Cloud (AWS, GCP, Azure, Firebase) · Databases (PostgreSQL, InfluxDB, MongoDB) · Visualisation (Power BI, Grafana, Dash, Streamlit).</p>

			<h3>IoT &amp; Hardware</h3>
			<p>End-to-end IoT architecture, Raspberry Pi, Arduino, PCB design, low-power sensor networks (MQTT, LoRA, OpenThread).</p>

			<h3>Finance &amp; Strategy</h3>
			<p>Project finance, infrastructure M&amp;A, financial modelling · Product lifecycle management, technology roadmapping, Agile project management, stakeholder communication.</p>

			<!-- Accomplishments -->
			<h2>Accomplishments &amp; Certifications</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Registered utility model <strong>ES1315071U</strong> — self-powered mechanical monitoring and predictive maintenance device.</li>
				<li>Hackathon Datafest 2025 (Santander &amp; Talent Hackers) — real-world business challenges on large datasets using NLP and deep learning.</li>
				<li>Project Akademia — Fundación Bankinter.</li>
				<li>Deep Learning Course — Fundación Universidad Carlos III.</li>
				<li>Master courses in aerodynamics, CFD and wind resource assessment — TU Delft.</li>
			</ul>

		</div>

		<!-- CTAs -->
		<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-10">
			<a
				class="btn-primary"
				href="/cv/CV Zee Marquez.pdf"
				download
				target="_blank"
			>
				Download CV
				<Icon height={20} name="mdi:arrow-collapse-down" />
			</a>
			<a
				class="btn-secondary"
				href="mailto:zeemarquez@outlook.com"
				target="_blank"
			>
				Get in touch
				<Icon height={20} name="mdi:email" />
			</a>
			<a
				class="btn-secondary"
				href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/zeemarquez"
				target="_blank"
				rel="noopener noreferrer"
			>
				LinkedIn
				<Icon height={20} name="mdi:linkedin" />
			</a>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
